de.payleven.inappsdk.listeners

Interface RemovePaymentInstrumentListener


  • public interface RemovePaymentInstrumentListener
    Listener that notifies when a payment instrument was removed from a use case based on the response from the backend In case of failure, a throwable containing the reason will be give as parameter

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onPaymentInstrumentRemovedSuccessfully()
      Called when the payment instrument was removed successfully
      void onPaymentInstrumentRemoveFailed(Throwable throwable)
      Called when the payment instrument removing failed

    • Method Detail

      • onPaymentInstrumentRemovedSuccessfully

        void onPaymentInstrumentRemovedSuccessfully()
        Called when the payment instrument was removed successfully

      • onPaymentInstrumentRemoveFailed

        void onPaymentInstrumentRemoveFailed(Throwable throwable)
        Called when the payment instrument removing failed
        Parameters:
        throwable - the error that caused the removing failure For more details on the reason of the failure check for the instance of the Throwable. If the Throwable is a CallbackError the error code and the message encapsulated can give more insight.

        Possible instances are:

        NetworkError - in case the error was caused by a network error

        MissingPaymentInstrumentsError if the PaymentInstrument parameter of the request was null

        InvalidUserTokenError if the request was called with an invalid user token
